# {LIBRARY_NAME} — Document Library / Content Pipeline

## What this is

{ONE_PARAGRAPH_DESCRIPTION}

A "document library" or "content pipeline" project — converts source specs/inputs into rendered output documents (HTML, PDF, slides, ebooks). Common shape:

```
source/        ← canonical specs (Markdown, YAML, JSON)
   ↓ render
build/         ← per-output formats (HTML, PDF, etc.)
   ↓ publish
output/        ← what gets distributed
```

## Tech stack

- **Source format:** {SOURCE_FORMAT} (e.g. "Markdown with YAML frontmatter", "AsciiDoc", "Pandoc-flavored markdown")
- **Renderer:** {RENDERER} (e.g. "Pandoc", "Sphinx", "MkDocs", "custom Python")
- **Templates:** {TEMPLATES_DIR}
- **Output formats:** {OUTPUT_FORMATS} (e.g. "HTML, PDF, EPUB")

